4 "§ 88B-4. Powers and duties of the Board.
5 (a) The Board shall have the following powers and duties:
6 (1) To administer and interpret this Chapter.
7 (2) To adopt, amend, and repeal rules to carry out the provisions of this Chapter.
8 (3) To examine and determine the qualifications and fitness of applicants for
9 licensure under this Chapter.
10 (4) To issue, renew, deny, restrict, suspend, or revoke licenses.
11 (5) To conduct investigations of alleged violations of this Chapter or the Board's
12 rules.
13 (6) To collect fees required by G.S. 88B-20 and any other monies permitted by
14 law to be paid to the Board.
15 (7) To approve new cosmetic art schools.
16 (7a) To adopt rules for cosmetic art schools.
17 (8) To inspect cosmetic art schools and shops.
18 (9) To adopt rules for the sanitary management and physical requirements of
19 cosmetic art shops and cosmetic art schools.
20 (10) To establish a curriculum for each course of study required for the issuance of
21 a license or certification issued under this Chapter.
22 (11) To employ an executive director and any additional professional, clerical, or
23 special personnel necessary to carry out the provisions of this Chapter, and to
24 purchase or rent necessary office space, equipment, and supplies.
25 (12) To adopt a seal.
26 (13) To carry out any other actions authorized by this Chapter.
27 (b) A member of the Board shall have the authority to inspect cosmetic art shops and
28 cosmetic art schools at any reasonable hour to determine compliance with the provisions of this
29 Chapter if the inspection is made: (i) at the request of the Board, or with the approval of the chair
30 or the executive director as the result of a complaint made to the Board or a problem reported by
31 an inspector, or (ii) at the request of an inspector who deems it necessary to request the assistance
32 of a Board member and who has the prior approval of the chair or executive director to do so. A
33 Board member who makes an inspection pursuant to this subsection shall file a report with the
34 Board before requesting reimbursement for expenses.
35 (c) The Board shall keep a record of its proceedings relating to the issuance, renewal,
36 denial, restriction, suspension, and revocation of licenses. licenses and certifications. This record
37 shall also contain each licensee's name, business and home addresses, license number, and the
38 date the license was issued.
39 (d) The Board shall offer or approve a 10-hour course in infection control for natural hair
40 care specialists. The Board shall make available at least one qualifying course on its website, free
41 of charge.
42 …
43 "§ 88B-7. Qualifications for licensing cosmetologists.
44 The Board shall issue a license to practice as a cosmetologist to any individual who meets all
45 of the following requirements:
46 (1) Successful completion of at least 1,500 1,200 hours of a cosmetology
47 curriculum in an approved cosmetic art school, or at least 1,200 hours of a
48 cosmetology curriculum in an approved cosmetic art school and completion
49 of an apprenticeship for a period of at least six months under the direct
50 supervision of a cosmetologist, as certified by sworn affidavit of three licensed
51 cosmetologists or by other evidence satisfactory to the Board.
