1 (a) The Board shall issue a temporary employment permit to an applicant for licensure
2 as an apprentice, a cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or
3 manicurist who meets all of the following:
4 (1) Has completed the required hours of a cosmetic art school curriculum in the
5 area in which the applicant wishes to be licensed.
6 (2) Has applied to take the examination within three months of completing the
7 required hours.
8 (3) Is qualified to take the examination.
9 (b) A temporary employment permit shall expire six months from the date of graduation
10 from a cosmetic art school and shall not be renewed.
11 (c) The holder of a temporary employment permit may practice cosmetic art only under
12 the supervision of a licensed cosmetologist, hair designer, manicurist, natural hair care specialist,
13 or esthetician, as appropriate, and may not operate a cosmetic art shop.
14 "§ 88B-13. Applicants licensed in other states.
15 (a) The Board shall issue a license to an applicant licensed as an apprentice, a
16 cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or manicurist in another
17 state if the applicant shows:
18 (1) The applicant is an active practitioner in good standing.
19 (2) The applicant has practiced at least one of the three years immediately
20 preceding the application for a license.
21 (3) There is no disciplinary proceeding or unresolved complaint pending against
22 the applicant at the time a license is to be issued by this State.
23 (4) The licensure requirements in the state in which the applicant is licensed are
24 substantially equivalent to those required by this State.
25 (b) Instead of meeting the requirements in subsection (a) of this section, any applicant
26 who is licensed as a cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or
27 manicurist in another state shall be admitted to practice in this State under the same reciprocity
28 or comity provisions that the state in which the applicant is licensed grants to persons licensed in
29 this State.
30 (c) The Board may establish standards for issuing a license to an applicant who is licensed
31 as a teacher in another state. These standards shall include a requirement that the licensure
32 requirements in the state in which the teacher is licensed shall be substantially equivalent to those
33 required in this State and that the applicant shall be licensed by the Board to practice in the area
34 in which the applicant is licensed to teach.
