34 "§ 88B-21. Renewals; expired licenses; inactive status.
35 (a) Each license to operate a cosmetic art shop shall be renewed on or before the first day
36 of February of each year. As provided in G.S. 88B-20, a late fee shall be charged for licenses
37 renewed after February 1. Any license not renewed by March 1 of each year shall expire. A
38 cosmetic art shop whose license has been expired for one year or less shall have the license
39 reinstated immediately upon payment of the reinstatement fee, the late fee, and all unpaid license
40 fees. The licensee shall submit to the Board, as a part of the renewal process, a list of all licensed
41 cosmetologists who practice cosmetic art in the shop and shall identify each as an employee or a
42 booth renter.
43 (b) Cosmetologist licenses shall be renewed on or before October 1 every three years
44 beginning October 1, 1998. A late fee shall be charged for renewals after that date. Any license
45 not renewed shall expire on October 1 of the year that renewal is required. The Board may
46 develop and implement a plan for staggered license renewal and may prorate license fees to
47 implement such a plan.
48 (c) Apprentice, Hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, and manicurist
49 licenses or certifications shall be renewed annually on or before October 1 of each year. A late
50 fee shall be charged for the renewal of licenses or certifications after that date. Any license or
51 certification not renewed shall expire on October 1 of that year.
