1 (d) Teacher licenses shall be renewed every two years on or before October 1. A late fee
2 shall be charged for the renewal of licenses after that date. Any license not renewed shall expire
3 on October 1 of that year.
4 (e) Prior to renewal of a certification or license, a teacher, cosmetologist, hair designer,
5 esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or manicurist shall annually complete eight four hours of
6 Board-approved continuing education for each year of the licensing cycle. A cosmetologist may
7 complete up to 24 hours 12 hours of required continuing education at any time within the
8 cosmetologist's three-year licensing cycle. Licensees shall submit written documentation to the
9 Board showing that they have satisfied the requirements of this subsection. A licensee who is in
10 active practice as a cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or
11 manicurist, has practiced for at least 10 consecutive years in that profession, and is 60 years of
12 age or older does not have to meet the continuing education requirements of this subsection. A
13 licensee who is in active practice as a cosmetologist cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician,
14 natural hair care specialist, or manicurist and has at least 20 consecutive years of experience as a
15 cosmetologist, does not have to meet the continuing education requirements of this subsection,
16 but shall report any continuing education classes completed to the Board, whether the continuing
17 education classes are Board-approved or not. Promotion of products and systems shall be allowed
18 at continuing education given in-house or at trade shows. Continuing education classes may also
19 be offered in secondary languages as needed. No member of the Board may offer continuing
20 education courses as required by this section.
21 (f) If an apprentice, a cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, manicurist, natural hair
22 care specialist, or teacher fails to renew his or her license or certification within five years
23 following the expiration date, the licensee shall be required to pass an examination as prescribed
24 by the Board before the license will be reinstated.
25 (g) Cosmetic art school licenses shall be renewed on or before October 1 of each year. A
26 late fee shall be charged for licenses renewed after that date. Any license not renewed by
27 November 1 of that year shall expire. A cosmetic art school whose license has been expired for
28 one year or less shall have its license reinstated upon payment of the reinstatement fee, the late
29 fee, and all unpaid license fees.
30 (h) Upon request by a licensee for inactive status, the Board may place the licensee's
31 name on the inactive list so long as the licensee is in good standing with the Board. An inactive
32 licensee is not required to complete continuing education requirements. An inactive licensee shall
33 not practice cosmetic art for consideration. However, the inactive licensee may continue to
34 purchase supplies as accorded an active licensee. When the inactive licensee desires to be
35 removed from the inactive list and return to active practice, the inactive licensee shall notify the
36 Board of his or her desire to return to active status and pay the required fee as determined by the
37 Board. As a condition of returning to active status, the Board may require the licensee to complete
38 eight to 24 hours of continuing education pursuant to subsection (e) of this section.
39 "§ 88B-22. Licenses and certifications required; criminal penalty.
40 (a) Except as provided in this Chapter, no person may practice or attempt to practice
41 cosmetic art for pay or reward in any form, either directly or indirectly, without being licensed
42 or certified as an apprentice, a cosmetologist, hair designer, esthetician, natural hair care
43 specialist, or manicurist by the Board.
44 (b) Except as provided in this Chapter, no person may practice cosmetic art or any part
45 of cosmetic art, for pay or reward in any form, either directly or indirectly, outside of a licensed
46 cosmetic art shop.
47 (c) No person may open or operate a cosmetic art shop in this State unless a license has
48 been issued by the Board for that shop.
49 (d) An individual certified or licensed as an esthetician, hair designer, natural hair care
50 specialist, or manicurist may practice only that part of cosmetic art for which the individual is
51 certified or licensed.
