16 "§ 88B-24. Revocation of licenses and other disciplinary measures.
17 The Board may restrict, suspend, revoke, or refuse to issue, renew, or reinstate any license
18 for any of the following:
19 (1) Conviction of a felony shown by certified copy of the record of the court of
20 conviction.
21 (2) Gross malpractice or gross incompetency as determined by the Board.
22 (3) Advertising by means of knowingly false or deceptive statements.
23 (4) Permitting any individual to practice cosmetic art without a license license,
24 infection control certification, or temporary employment permit, with an
25 expired license or temporary employment permit, or with an invalid license
26 license, infection control certification, or temporary employment permit.
27 (5) Obtaining or attempting to obtain a license for money or other thing of value
28 other than the required fee or by fraudulent misrepresentation.
29 (6) Practicing or attempting to practice by fraudulent misrepresentation.
30 (7) Willful failure to display a certificate of license or an infection control
31 certification as required by G.S. 88B-23.
32 (8) Willful violation of the rules adopted by the Board.
33 (9) Violation of G.S. 86A-15 G.S. 86B-31 by a cosmetologist, hair designer,
34 esthetician, natural hair care specialist, or manicurist licensed or certified by
35 the Board and practicing cosmetic art in a barber shop.
